         <abstract>
            <p>Construction of Gauss quadratures with prescribed knots via Jacobi matrices is extended to the case where not all orthogonal polynomials exist due to the weight function changing sign. An algorithm is described and is demonstrated by calculating the knots of Kronrod schemes and other Gauss quadratures with prescribed knots.</p>
          </abstract>
